Accounts.Name: Accounts Receivable
Accounts.Description: Outstanding invoices the company has issued out to the client but has not yet received in cash at balance date.

Accounts.Name: Prepayments
Accounts.Description: An expenditure that has been paid for in advance.

Accounts.Name: Inventory
Accounts.Description: Value of tracked inventory items for resale.

Accounts.Name: Office Equipment
Accounts.Description: Office equipment that is owned and controlled by the business

Accounts.Name: Less Accumulated Depreciation on Office Equipment
Accounts.Description: The total amount of office equipment cost that has been consumed by the entity (based on the useful life)

Accounts.Name: Computer Equipment
Accounts.Description: Computer equipment that is owned and controlled by the business

Accounts.Name: Less Accumulated Depreciation on Computer Equipment
Accounts.Description: The total amount of computer equipment cost that has been consumed by the business (based on the useful life)

Accounts.Name: Accounts Payable
Accounts.Description: Outstanding invoices the company has received from suppliers but has not yet paid at balance date

Accounts.Name: Accruals
Accounts.Description: Any services the business has received but have not yet been invoiced for e.g. Accountancy Fees

Accounts.Name: Unpaid Expense Claims
Accounts.Description: Expense claims typically made by employees/shareholder employees still outstanding.

Accounts.Name: Wages Payable
Accounts.Description: Xero automatically updates this account for payroll entries created using Payroll and will store the payroll amount to be paid to the employee for the pay run. This account enables you to maintain separate accounts for employee Wages Payable amounts and Accounts Payable amounts

Accounts.Name: Sales Tax
Accounts.Description: The balance in this account represents Sales Tax owing to or from your tax authority. At the end of the tax period, it is this account that should be used to code against either the 'refunds from' or 'payments to' your tax authority that will appear on the bank statement. Xero has been designed to use only one sales tax account to track sales taxes on income and expenses, so there is no need to add any new sales tax accounts to Xero.

Accounts.Name: Employee Tax Payable
Accounts.Description: The amount of tax that has been deducted from wages or salaries paid to employes and is due to be paid

Accounts.Name: Income Tax Payable
Accounts.Description: The amount of income tax that is due to be paid, also resident withholding tax paid on interest received.

Accounts.Name: Suspense
Accounts.Description: An entry that allows an unknown transaction to be entered, so the accounts can still be worked on in balance and the entry can be dealt with later.

Accounts.Name: Historical Adjustment
Accounts.Description: For accountant adjustments

Accounts.Name: Rounding
Accounts.Description: An adjustment entry to allow for rounding

Accounts.Name: Tracking Transfers
Accounts.Description: Transfers between tracking categories

Accounts.Name: Loan
Accounts.Description: Money that has been borrowed from a creditor

Accounts.Name: Owners Contribution
Accounts.Description: Funds contributed by the owner

Accounts.Name: Owners Draw
Accounts.Description: Withdrawals by the owners

Accounts.Name: Retained Earnings
Accounts.Description: Do not Use

Accounts.Name: Common Stock
Accounts.Description: The value of shares purchased by the shareholders

Accounts.Name: Sales
Accounts.Description: Income from any normal business activity

Accounts.Name: Other Revenue
Accounts.Description: Any other income that does not relate to normal business activities and is not recurring

Accounts.Name: Interest Income
Accounts.Description: Interest income

Accounts.Name: Cost of Goods Sold
Accounts.Description: Costs of goods made by the business include material, labor, and other modification costs.

Accounts.Name: Advertising
Accounts.Description: Expenses incurred for advertising while trying to increase sales

Accounts.Name: Bank Service Charges
Accounts.Description: Fees charged by your bank for transactions regarding your bank account(s).

Accounts.Name: Janitorial Expenses
Accounts.Description: Expenses incurred for cleaning business property.

Accounts.Name: Consulting & Accounting
Accounts.Description: Expenses related to paying consultants

Accounts.Name: Entertainment
Accounts.Description: Expenses paid by company for the business but are not deductable for income tax purposes.

Accounts.Name: Postage & Delivery
Accounts.Description: Expenses incurred on postage & delivery costs.

Accounts.Name: General Expenses
Accounts.Description: General expenses related to the running of the business.

Accounts.Name: Insurance
Accounts.Description: Expenses incurred for insuring the business' assets

Accounts.Name: Legal Expenses
Accounts.Description: Expenses incurred on any legal matters

Accounts.Name: Utilities
Accounts.Description: Expenses incurred for lighting, powering or heating the premises

Accounts.Name: Automobile Expenses
Accounts.Description: Expenses incurred on the running of company automobiles.

Accounts.Name: Office Expenses
Accounts.Description: General expenses related to the running of the business office.

Accounts.Name: Printing & Stationery
Accounts.Description: Expenses incurred by the entity as a result of printing and stationery

Accounts.Name: Rent
Accounts.Description: The payment to lease a building or area.

Accounts.Name: Repairs and Maintenance
Accounts.Description: Expenses incurred on a damaged or run down asset that will bring the asset back to its original condition.

Accounts.Name: Wages and Salaries
Accounts.Description: Payment to employees in exchange for their resources

Accounts.Name: Payroll Tax Expense
Accounts.Description: The amount of payroll tax that is due to be paid

Accounts.Name: Dues & Subscriptions
Accounts.Description: E.g. Magazines, professional bodies

Accounts.Name: Telephone & Internet
Accounts.Description: Expenditure incurred from any business-related phone calls, phone lines, or internet connections

Accounts.Name: Travel
Accounts.Description: Expenses incurred from travel which has a business purpose

Accounts.Name: Bad Debts
Accounts.Description: Noncollectable accounts receivable which have been written off.

Accounts.Name: Depreciation
Accounts.Description: The amount of the asset's cost (based on the useful life) that was consumed during the period

Accounts.Name: Income Tax Expense
Accounts.Description: A percentage of total earnings paid to the government.

Accounts.Name: Interest Expense
Accounts.Description: Any interest expenses paid to your tax authority, business bank accounts or credit card accounts.

Accounts.Name: Bank Revaluations
Accounts.Description: Bank account revaluations due for foreign exchange rate changes

Accounts.Name: Unrealized Currency Gains
Accounts.Description: Unrealized gains on outstanding items

Accounts.Name: Realized Currency Gains
Accounts.Description: Gains or losses made due to currency exchange rates

Accounts.Name: Revenue Received in Advance
Accounts.Description: When customers have paid in advance of work/services.
